"title": "4266: sea",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4266",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>The sea created and controlled by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:9-Gen1:10\">GEN 1:9–1:10</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:22\">JER 5:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:5\">PSA 95:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:29\">PSA 107:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps146:6\">PSA 146:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:2\">ISA 50:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:8\">AMO 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:6\">AMO 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:24\">ACT 4:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:15\">ACT 14:15</a></p>\n<h2>Creatures of the sea</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:25\">PSA 104:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:21\">GEN 1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:8\">PSA 8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:20\">EZK 38:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:3\">HOS 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:14\">HAB 1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Sea monsters sometimes represented spiritual forces</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:13\">PSA 74:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job26:12\">JOB 26:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:1\">ISA 27:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:1\">REV 13:1</a></p>\n<h2>The sea represented hidden depths</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:3\">AMO 9:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:16\">2SA 22:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:16\">JOB 38:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:19\">MIC 7:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:6\">MAT 18:6</a></p>\n<h2>Named seas</h2>\n<h3>The Red, or Reed, Sea</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:19\">EXO 10:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:29\">HEB 11:29</a></p>\n<h3>The Dead, or Salt, Sea</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:3\">GEN 14:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:25\">2KI 14:25</a></p>\n<h3>The Sea of Galilee</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:11\">NUM 34:11</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:1\">JHN 6:1</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The Great, or Mediterranean, Sea</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:6-Num34:7\">NUM 34:6–34:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:10\">EZK 47:10</a></p>\n<h3>The Adriatic Sea</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:27\">ACT 27:27</a></strong> <em>In NT times referring to an area extending south of the present Adriatic Sea.</em></p>\n<h2>The Sea before the temple</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:23-1Kgs7:26\">1KI 7:23–7:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:39\">1KI 7:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:17\">2KI 16:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:13\">2KI 25:13</a></p>\n<h2>The sea before the throne</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:6\">REV 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:2\">REV 15:2</a></p>\n<h2>Metaphorical references to the sea</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:12\">ISA 17:12</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:6\">JAS 1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:12\">JOB 7:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job11:9\">JOB 11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:11-Job14:12\">JOB 14:11–14:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps93:4\">PSA 93:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:30\">ISA 5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:9\">ISA 11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:18\">ISA 48:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:20\">ISA 57:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:23\">JER 6:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:23\">JER 49:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:42\">JER 50:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:42\">JER 51:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:13\">LAM 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:3\">EZK 26:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:11\">ZEC 10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:13\">JUD 1:13</a></p>\n<h2>No more sea</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1\">REV 21:1</a></strong></p>",
